~ 1 Thessalonians 1 ~

|1| Paul and Silvanus [^Silvanus^ is the Greek variant of ^Silas^] and Timothy {Acts 16:1; 2 Thessalonians 1:1; Acts 15:22}
to the church of ^the^ Thessalonians in God ^the^ Father, and ^the^ Lord Jesus
Christ: Grace to you and peace from God ^our^ Father and ^the^ Lord Jesus
Christ. [final clause that starts with ^from God^ not found in all manuscripts] {Romans 1:7; 1 Peter 5:12}

= Thanksgiving for Faith =

|2| We give thanks to God always [or ^without ceasing^] {Ephesians 5:20; 2 Thessalonians 1:3} concerning you all, {Romans 1:8}
making mention of you ^in^ [literally ^on^] our prayers, {Romans 1:10; 2 Timothy 1:3; Romans 1:9}
|3| unceasingly remembering your work of faith, {James 2:14-26; John 6:29} and the labor of love, {Galatians 5:6; 2 Thessalonians 1:11} and the
patience [or ^perseverance^ or ^steadfastness^] of hope {1 Corinthians 13:13; Romans 8:25; Romans 15:4} ^in^ [literally ^of^]
our Lord, Jesus Christ, before [or ^in the sight of^ or ^in the presence of^]
our God and Father, [final clause that starts with ^before^ not found in all
manuscripts]

|4| knowing, brothers
[the plural of the Greek word ^adelphoi^ here translated as ^brothers^
refers to siblings in a family; depending on context, ^adelphoi^ may refer
either to men or to both men and women who are siblings; word also appears in
2:1, 9, 14, 17; 3:7; 4:1, 10, 13; 5:1, 4, 12, 14, 25, 27]
{Colossians 3:12} ^who are^ [literally ^having been^] loved by God, {2 Thessalonians 2:13} your
election {Romans 1:7; 2 Peter 1:10}
|5| because our gospel {2 Thessalonians 2:14; 2 Corinthians 2:12} ^did^ not came to you in word only, but also in power, {1 Thessalonians 2:10; 1 Corinthians 2:4; Romans 15:19}
and in ^the^ Holy Spirit, and ^with^ [literlaly ^in^] much assurance, as you
know what sort we were among you because of you. {Luke 1:1}
|6| And you became imitators of us and of the Lord, {2 Timothy 4:2} welcoming the word in
affliction with much joy of ^the^ Holy Spirit, {1 Corinthians 11:1; Galatians 5:22; 1 Corinthians 4:16; Acts 13:52}
|7| so ^that^ you become patterns {1 Timothy 4:12} to all those believing in Macedonia and
Achaia. {Acts 16:9; Acts 18:12; Romans 15:26}
|8| For the word of the Lord sounded from you, not only in Macedonia and
Achaia, but also in every place your faith toward God has gone ^forth^,
[literally ^out^] {2 Corinthians 2:14; Romans 16:19; 2 Thessalonians 3:1; Romans 1:8; Romans 10:18} so ^there is^ no need for us to have to ^say^ [literally
^speak^] anything.
|9| For ^they^ themselves announce about us what kind of ^reception^ [literally
^entrance^] we have ^with^ you, and how you had turned to God from the idols, {1 Corinthians 12:2; Galatians 4:8}
to serve ^the^ living and true God, {Acts 14:15; Matthew 16:16; John 17:3}
|10| and to await the His Son from the heavens, {1 Corinthians 1:7} whom He raised from ^the^ dead,
Jesus. {Acts 2:24; Acts 1:11} He delivers us from the coming wrath. {Romans 1:18; 1 Thessalonians 5:9; Colossians 1:13; Romans 5:9; 1 Thessalonians 2:16; Matthew 3:7}
